reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on November 30, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Great desk, amazing value!
reviews.reviewText: I'm blown away by how nice this desk is for the price. Assembly took no time at all and it was incredibly easy to follow the directions. Extremely sturdy and well made even if the materials aren't the highest of quality. Doesn't wobble at all. It is a little smaller than I expected, though, but I actually prefer that. The lights are very nice! If you're on the fence about buying this, I highly recommend it. It looks and feels twice the price I paid for it, minimum.

reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Love the look & feel!!
reviews.reviewText: I love my desk very much! It fits everything I need on it in an organized way. My desk is modern, beautiful, functional, minimalist and fits in the small space I have without looking cluttered! The lights are great for setting the mood and atmosphere to what I want!

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 14, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 4.0 out of 5 stars Good value for basic desk
reviews.reviewText: You can’t really expect much for around 100.00. This desk is pretty well made for the price. The instructions were clear and everything you needed was included except for s hammer. My only issue is that the product was slightly damaged in transit. The damage was not bad enough to return it.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on September 24, 2023
reviews.reviewText: i love it. i was worried it would look like the picture and the desk actually be blue, but its not. the gray black color is flattering, it is so easy to assemble, it is lightweight and easy to move. the blue is just from the pretty lights that flash, which you can turn off. so convenient. i love the convenience of having both my phones and both computers as well as smart watch plugged into the desk at once. great buy

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 13, 2024
reviews.reviewText: If you are on a budget and okay with flimsy desk then go for it, but I do not recommend the quality of this desk. It was easy to assemble and came with all the parts and pieces, but it rocks. The monitor stand is not sturdy enough to hold my Samsung ultra wide monitor. It is also painted cheaply that you can see some raw edges. Just spend the extra $20-$30 and get a better one. A lot of good reviews on here that prompted me to choose this desk. I wish I had spent the extra $20 and got the first one I liked.
